-- Barclays Bank’s Ugandan Unit Full-Year Profit More Than Doubles
-- B y   F r e d   O j a m b o
-- 2012-04-16T05:12:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-16/barclays-bank-s-ugandan-unit-full-year-profit-more-than-doubles.html
Barclays Plc (BARC) ’s Ugandan unit said
full-year profit more than doubled after it reduced bad loans
and boosted customer deposits.  Net income climbed to 21.2 billion shillings ($21.2
billion) in the 12 months through December from 9.7 billion
shillings a year earlier, Barclays Bank Uganda Ltd., based in
Kampala, said today in a statement published in the New Vision
newspaper. Impairment losses on loans and advances fell 33
percent to 14.1 billion shillings, it said.  Customer deposits climbed 2.2 percent to 906 billion
shillings, according to the statement. Net interest income, the
money banks earn from interest charges on loans, rose 9.8
percent to 86.4 billion shillings, the bank said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Ojambo in Kampala at 
